Twenty-four firefighters are currently on scene, while three helicopters are also assisting with water bombing efforts. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town firefighters are currently battling a vegetation fire on Signall Hill.The blaze broke out more than an hour ago.Twenty-four firefighters are currently on scene, while three helicopters are also assisting with water bombing efforts.The City's Fire and Rescue Services' Theo Layne says: The fire is fanned by a very strong south-easterly wind. There s no immediate danger to property. The cause of the fire is undetermined at this stage. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)